# In-App Messaging & Health Reports Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
The objective is to implement **In-App Messaging** between patients and providers, and allow both parties to export **Generate Health Reports (PDFs)** for record-keeping and offline review.

We will achieve this by building new database models in the Django backend for messages, creating chat interfaces in Flutter, and utilizing Flutter's `pdf` packages to generate visually appealing reports completely on the client side (preventing Render server overloads).

## Proposed Changes

### Django Backend Architecture
#### [MODIFY] [backend/api/models.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/models.py), [serializers.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/serializers.py), [urls.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/urls.py), [views.py](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/views.py)
- Add a new [Message](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/backend/api/models.py#35-47) model:
  ```python
  class Message(models.Model):
      sender_id = models.CharField(max_length=100) # 'provider' or 'patient_xxx'
      receiver_id = models.CharField(max_length=100)
      content = models.TextField()
      timestamp = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)
      is_read = models.BooleanField(default=False)
  ```
- Build standard REST endpoints for checking unread messages, sending texts, and fetching chat history.
- Run `python manage.py makemigrations` and migrate.

---

### Export Reports (PDF Generation)
*To save server load and support true "offline generation" for patients in remote areas, PDFs will be generated locally on the phone using Flutter.*

#### [MODIFY] [mobile/pubspec.yaml](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/pubspec.yaml) & [dashboard/pubspec.yaml](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/pubspec.yaml)
- Add dependencies: `pdf`, `printing`, `path_provider`

#### [NEW] shared utility: [pdf_generator.dart](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/lib/utils/pdf_generator.dart) (Mobile & Dashboard)
- A unified robust class that accepts a list of `CheckinModel` or [Patient](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/lib/services/api_service.dart#4-37) data, and renders a visually beautiful PDF document with the Mint/Teal color branding.
- The PDF will contain: Patient ID, Condition, Overall Average Risk, and a Table log of the last 30 check-ins (Date, Risk Level, Meds Taken).

#### [MODIFY] [mobile/lib/screens/history_screen.dart](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/lib/screens/history_screen.dart)
- Append a floating action button or top right action: "📄 Generate Report".

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart)
- Inside the detailed patient view (right panel), add a button beneath the patient's stats: "⬇️ Download PDF Medical Report".

---

### In-App Messaging Feature
*Since Render free tier drops long-running connections like WebSockets, we will use a standard HTTP Polling strategy every 15 seconds while the user is actively on the [MessagesScreen](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/lib/screens/messages_screen.dart#8-14).*

#### [NEW] [mobile/lib/screens/messages_screen.dart](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/mobile/lib/screens/messages_screen.dart)
- A standard chat interface mimicking WhatsApp/iMessage clean aesthetics. Bubbles on right (Patient/Self), Bubbles on left (Provider/Doctor).
- Tie this into the Mobile bottom navigation bar.

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart](file:///c:/dev/projects/health_tracker_system/dashboard/lib/screens/dashboard_screen.dart)
- Introduce a messaging modal/drawer. When a provider selects a patient from the main table, they can tab over to "Messages" to quickly
### Implementation Constraints
- Backend: Django REST Framework with Simple JWT (if authentication is required).
- Frontend: Flutter
- Data source: Use Hive for local mobile persistence, HTTP calls to interact with Django API.

